cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes an exemplar-based approach that transfers learning from previously known concepts, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also introduces an efficient matching scheme for search and retrieval, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
